You let yourself breathe for a second. Then you get back to work. By every measure, Sentinel is doing what it's supposed to do. It's protecting people. The logs make that pretty clear. But you can't shake the feeling of how much power this thing has. You know better than anyone that it cuts both ways. Every success comes with the possibility of something going terribly wrong.

